                    <ab>(C.) In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/252">Arnolfus</persName> divina favente
                        clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Cognoscat
                        generale collegium omnium fidelium nostrorum praesentium scilicet atque
                        futurorum, quia <persName ref="#people/1651" key="#Abbots">Petrus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abba</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobii</rs> in honore <orgName
                            key="#Houses #Curtes #Manentes #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches #Monasteries #Cells/hermitages #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/301">sancti Salvatoris in <placeName
                                ref="#places/737" key="#Monasteries">monte
                            Amiato</placeName></orgName> constructi quoddam praeceptum detulit ad
                        manus nostras bonae memoriae domni <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/110">Hludouuici</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatoris</rs> per <rs key="#Intercessory"
                            >interventum</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #Archbishops" ref="#people/1652"
                            >Hathonis</persName> venerabilis atque dilectissimi <rs
                            key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> nostri deprecans clementiam
                        nostram, ut hoc nostra auctoritate roboraremus. Continebatur autem in eodem
                            <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">praecepto</rs>, qualiter ante libatus
                        domnus Hludouuicus imperator illud cenobium cuidam <rs key="#fidelisOf"
                            >fideli suo</rs>
                        <persName key="#fidelisOf" ref="#people/1514">Adalpreht</persName> nominato
                        ad regendum commisit, ipse autem ob incuriam eorum, qui ipsum monasterium
                        prius providere debebant, cum fratres ibidem domino militantes inopia
                        cuiuscumque boni confectos et divina obsequia neglecta penitusque collapsa
                        repperisset, eorundem fratrum usibus haec loca contulit, ut sufficientiam
                        victus et habitus habentes regulariter vivere et sine alicuius animositatis
                        impedimento divinis laudibus sana mente insistere quivissent, hoc est <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1512"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1949">sancti Benedicti</placeName></orgName>, <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curte</rs> de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/334"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/764">Palea</placeName></geogName>, <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/303">sancti Stephani in <placeName
                                ref="#places/757"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Monticlo</placeName></orgName> et cellam sanctae <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/302">Mariae in <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/756">Lamulas</placeName></orgName>, curticellam de
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/331"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/760">Mustia</placeName></geogName> nec non curticellam
                        de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/335"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/1951">Titinano</placeName></geogName> et in <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants #Angaria"
                            ref="#places/1952">Cerri</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Coloni/tenants #Angaria">angariales</rs> seu in <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Manentes"
                            ref="#places/761"><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Manentes"
                                ref="#estates/2315">Feroniano</geogName></placeName> et <rs
                            key="#Manentes">manentes</rs> eius, insuper cellam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/308">sancti Salvatoris de <placeName
                                ref="#places/762"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                                >vale Rachana</placeName></orgName> et curticellam de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/332">Cuniclo</geogName> cum ipso gagiolo de <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/1953">Portiano</placeName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1455">cellam <placeName key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/1948"
                                >sancti Stephani</placeName>
                        </orgName> in <placeName ref="#places/430">Terquini</placeName> et cellam
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1513">sancti Seueri</orgName> super <rs
                            key="#Lakes">lacum</rs> cum ipsa curticellula de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/333"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/1956">Bisentio</placeName></geogName>, cellam etiam
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1514"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1955">sancti Miniati</placeName></orgName> cum cellula
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1515">sanctae Mariae de <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/2734">Ualeriano</placeName></orgName> cum ipsis
                            <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#estates/2346">rebus de <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1964">Curticula</placeName></geogName> et omnibus
                        pertinentiis et appendiciis suis, ea videlicet ratione ut ipsum collegium
                        cenobitarum haec omnia suis tantummodo utilitatibus habentes indeque victum
                        et habitum regulariter percipientes absque murmurio divinis die noctuque
                        vacarent obsequiis; sed praefatus vir ut hoc, quod bono studio ac zelo
                        divino fecit, perennem stabilitatem teneret, precatus est clementiam iam
                        dicti imperatoris, hanc collationem ut cum suae auctoritatis scripto
                        roboraret atque firmaret, quod et ita fecit, veluti in eodem praecepto
                        scriptum habetur. At nos huiusmodi iustae ac rationabili petitioni libenter
                        annuentes hoc nostrae munificentiae praeceptum conscribi iussimus, per quod
                        decernimus atque firmissime iubemus, ut ipsa collectio fratrum omnes res
                        ante titulatas sine inquietudine et absque ulla publica repetitione aut
                        rectoris loci ipsius subtractu in suos usus ac necessitates habeant ordinent
                        et disponant, quatenus inde sufficientiam habentes divinis laudibus
                        insistere atque pro nostra omniumque christianae religionis salute melius
                        delectet orare. Â  Insuper etiam ante dicti abbatis et fratrum suo regimini
                        subditorum sub regulari disciplina secum domino servientum rogatu ipsum
                        monasterium cum eodem abbate et omni ipsa monachorum turba omnibusque
                        hominibus vel rebus ad ipsum cenobium rite pertinentibus pro remedio animae
                        nostrae parentumque nostrorum in nostrum <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">mundiburdum ac defensionem</rs>
                        suscipimus. Et idcirco praecipientes iubemus, ut nullus de fidelibus nostris
                        comes missus aut iudex vel de iudiciaria potestate in villas seu curtes seu
                        loca ipsius monasterii tam per donationes vel confirmationes regum quamque
                        etiam per bonorum hominum largitatem ipsi monasterio collata seu quolibet
                        iusto studio augmentata ad ipsam casam dei legibus aspicientia ad causas
                        audiendas vel freda exigenda seu fideiussores tollendos sive mansiones aut
                        paratas faciendas aut ullas publicas redibitiones vel functiones requirendas
                        quoquo tempore invadere aut ingredi ullatenus praesumat, sed nostro
                        mundiburdo et defensione ipsa domus dei quieta tranquillitae potiatur.
                        Similiter ecclesias illas ad ipsum coenobium pertinentes, id est <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> sancti <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1511"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches"
                                ref="#places/1944">Petri in Carmarita</placeName></orgName> atque
                            <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellulam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1454"><placeName ref="#places/1947"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                                >sancti Sauini</placeName></orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1452"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1946">sanctae Restitutae</placeName></orgName> vel
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1456"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1945">sancti Petri</placeName></orgName> seu et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1455"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1948">sancti Stephani</placeName></orgName> in
                            <placeName ref="#places/430">Terquino</placeName> cum omnibus rebus
                        parvis aut magnis, quaecumque dici seu nominari possunt, praesenti tempore
                        illuc aspicientibus seu quas inantea divina clementia in augmentum ipsius
                        sepe nominati monasterii venire concesserit, sub nostrum mundiburdum ac
                        tuitionem assumentes simile pactum confirmamus. Pari modo etiam concedimus,
                        ut quando quidem abba ipsius cenobii de hac luce divina iussione
                        discesserit, habeant licentiam inter se eligendi abbatem de eadem
                        collectione, quemcumque inter se caeteris digniorem et promptiorem indagare
                        potuerint ad dei familiam divinitus gubernandam et nostram servitutem
                        humanitus peragendam. Si autem, quod absit, quaevis mortalium persona
                        temerario ausu huius praecepti violatrix existere conata fuerit, coepti sui
                        inops <rs key="#Penalty">centum libras defecati auri</rs> coacta persolvat,
                            <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem camerae palatii nostri</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">alteram partem, quibus iniuria
                            facta est</rs>. Et ut hoc praeceptum absque omni inquietudine in sua
                        soliditate stabile perseveret, manu nostra illud firmavimus ac more nostro
                        insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Arnolfi (MF.) invictissimi imperatoris
                        augusti. <persName key="#Archchancellor" ref="#people/1614"
                            >Uuichingus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarius</rs> advicem <persName
                            key="#Archchaplain" ref="#people/1613">Theotmari</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchaplain">archicappellani</rs> recognovit et (SR. NN.) (SI.
                        D.) Data IIII kal. MAR. die anno incarnationis domini DCCCXCVI, indictionum
                        XIIII, anno regni Arnolfi regis in Frantia VIIII, in Italia III; actum
                            <placeName ref="#places/52">Romae</placeName>; in dei nomine feliciter
                        amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
